 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 934<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/03 11:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Now this is wrong </span><hr size=1> No problem with that here.  If a company can make money by relocating overseas, they should do that.  It's called capitalism.  It's their job to make money.  If we can't compete in some line of business, due to labor costs or whatever else, we should get out of that line of business and focus on something we can compete in.  Falsely subsidizing a non competitive business is uncapitalistic.<br>
<br>
Ammelen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=herdervazaelle>HerderVazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 2159<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/03 12:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ummm</span><hr size=1> Ammelen, you're ok with taxpayers funding contracts to companies with corporate hq's overseas to avoid paying taxes?<br>
<br>
Theres no subsidizing here, its just plain tax evasion.  They are american companies who aren't paying taxes because high ranking republicans are stopping legislation that would allow them to not bid on gov't contracts.  <br>
<br>
It's the good ole boy system. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 938<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/03 12:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ummm</span><hr size=1> As long as the contracts are the best we can get, yes.  The government should simply solicit bids for any job that needs to be done.  They should go with the lowest bid that they are confident can/will do the job adequately.<br>
<br>
There is nothing wrong with using subtleties of international law to reduce the tax burden on a company.  My parents have done this as my father has spent a lot of time working overseas (Europe mostly).  There are quite a few subtleties of tax law that reduce your taxes substantially when you live overseas.<br>
<br>
I don't support any form of legislation at all whatsoever that increases taxation on anyone or anything.  Period.  Taxes are already way too high and need to be dramatically slashed to be brought into line with a more libertarian approach to government.<br>
<br>
Ammelen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=truthreason>TruthReason</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I'm actually Goanad.</span><br>  Posts: 1253<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/03 1:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Now this is wrong </span><hr size=1> Honestly Herder....this issue would be a little moot if I had my way in regard to Taxation. I do not think there is logic to sustain taxing corporation AND then taxing the same profits again for individuals. I would like to see a revenue neutral amendment to the Tax Code that would remove taxation from industry and place a one time taxation on Dividends paid to stockholders. Again it should be revenue neutral. <br>
<br>
Finally, it's not too much to expect that US tax dollars go to US companies. You have to ask at some point who exactly is serving whom?  You need to match your battlefield patriotism with your pocketbook patriotism, imho. All this means practically speaking is that if you move your HQ overseas don't expect your gov't contract to move w/ you. NO biggie right?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 941<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/03 3:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Now this is wrong </span><hr size=1> I don't want the government spending more of my taxpayer dollars on a contract regardless of what the company is doing to reduce costs.<br>
<br>
The corporation's only loyalty is to its stockholders, period.<br>
<br>
The goal of the government should be to reduce spending.<br>
<br>
Ammelen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=truthreason>TruthReason</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I'm actually Goanad.</span><br>  Posts: 1257<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/03 4:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Now this is wrong </span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> The goal of the government should be to reduce spending. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You, Herder, Ayiar, and I might all have different ideas of what the proper role of the government is in society, but certainly if there is to be any government them surely it's objective must be something other than to remove itself from existence, per your quote, no? <br>
<br>
In many ways, from an economists point of view, this dances around the issue of what is the proper rate of taxation?  What level is most optimal? Beyond the fact that this is an inherently political question, some have tried to portray it differently. <br>
<br>
In fact, one person, on a napkin without any empirical evidence, constructed a curve in such a way as to posit that we are overtaxed and that furthermore, and due to the slope of the curve, should we reduce taxation, we'd experience revenue windfalls. That economic philosophy continues to haunt us. Federal deficits ballooned because of that philosophy. We should ask when will economists will stop engaging in politics and stop putting forth guesswork in the place of well established research. <br>
<br>
How much is the right amount of government? It's a political question and should be answered as such.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tuvanvaz>TuvanVaz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 586<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/03 4:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://nightblade.netfirms.com/linkbanners/OABanner.gif height=33 width=88></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Now this is wrong </span><hr size=1> It happens all the time.<br>
<br>
Companies that operate in PA are incorporated under Delaware laws because of the lower tax rate on them.  Does that mean that PA shouldn't do business with them?<br>
<br>
The employees of the firms in question are still US citizens.  We should discrimiate from them because their corporations aren't funding the US government?<br>
<br>
Sounds like a bribe in a way.  &quot;Pay us money so you can get a contract....&quot;<br>
<br>
The Government should be looking for ways to cut costs.  <br>
