<br>
The Republicans get into office by stating the goal of reducing government spending, yet the only administration in my lifetime to actually reduce goverment spending in relation to GDP was run by the Democrats.<br>
<br>
Bush the Second is now in office.  Taxation for the rich is going to be less (to my benefit) while the poor will shoulder the same burden as before.  My guess is they will actually pay more, because local governments will be forced to raise the tax rates -- especially sales taxes -- which hit the lower income people harder than the moderate-to-high income brackets.<br>
<br>
Warren Buffet chastised the Bush administration for the outrageously massive tax break that will be given to the rich.  Under the original Bush tax reductions Warren Buffet's effective tax rate would have gone from about 30 percent to a mere 3 percent, while the middle class workers he employs would have maintained the same effective tax rate.<br>
<br>
Taxing dividends of the idle rich is no more a &quot;double taxation&quot; than a paycheck is to a normal wage earner.<br>
<br>
I can only hope that Warren Buffet does the same thing with his new windfall that I am doing with mine -- donating it to political candidates that will oppose the selfish, horrendous fiscal policy that the Republicans are enacting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=truthreason>TruthReason</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I'm actually Goanad.</span><br>  Posts: 1259<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/03 5:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Now this is wrong </span><hr size=1> I dont see the irony Anywon. I've never been a supporter of GOP fiscal policy. Indeed it's THE reason why they will never represent me. <br>
<br>
George Herbert Walker Bush indeed said supply side economics were &quot;voodoo&quot; economics in a fleeting moment of contrituion whilst in the middle of a run for his parties presidential nomination. Of course he later fell into lockstep with the party on the issue and thus prostituted the well considered thinking results of his economics training. <br>
<br>
Of course Warren Buffet is right. He was basically catching the GOP redhanded in the act of making a political payoff to the minority of Americans who elected dubya.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 944<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/03 6:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Now this is wrong </span><hr size=1> I don't see how anyone can even begin to make an argument that the poor shoulder the majority of the burden.  Just look at the numbers, the rich carry the country.  You can argue that it should be this way (I disagree), but anyone sane will realize that the rich already pay for everyone else as it is.  The poor just mooch.  (Translation: The rich pay more in taxes than they receive in benefits, the poor pay less in taxes than they receive in benefits.)<br>
<br>
As for the role of government Goanad, you sort of took me out of context.  I'm not stating that the only purpose of govt should be to eliminate itself.  I was stating, more specifically, that when choosing contracts, the government should choose the ones with the lowest pricetags.  i.e. Given some fixed benefit to be received, the government's goal should be reduction of cost.  It was not meant to be as broad a statement as you read it to be.<br>
<br>
I believe that government should seek to shrink itself to a minimal size, but not eliminate itself.  I'd like to see our national budget about 10 percent of what it is and most programs eliminated outside of national defense.<br>
<br>
Ammelen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=anywon>Anywon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I can't decide on a title</span><br>  Posts: 740<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/27/03 6:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: now this is wrong</span><hr size=1> Ammelen, you are basically stating:<br>
